  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Black Quotidian: Everyday History in African-American Newspapers (2019), published by Stanford University Press. Scholarly uptake (strength 0.6). 10 citations \u2014 measurable academic uptake.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Black Quotidian: Everyday History in African-American Newspapers was published by Stanford University Press in 2019. Conceptually, the work connects to Newspaper, History, Geography, Ethnology and Genealogy.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">OpenAlex records 10 citations. Citations peaked in 2023 with 8 citing works. Notable citing venues include Faculty Digital Archive (New York University Florence) and Bloomsbury Academic eBooks. Inferred role: Scholarly uptake.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Beyond citations, current data shows limited visible usage or public discussion yet.</p>",
